name: Flying Air Canada's SMALLEST Dash 8! Calgary to Edmonton on the Dash 8-100
description:
Subscribe to Vuelogs: https://www.youtube.com/vuelogs

The Dash 8-100 is the smallest variant of the Dash 8 family, seating just 37 passengers. Several operators have flown these on behalf of Air Canada since the late 1980s, but until the end of October this year, they only flew out of Eastern Canada. 

These are planned to be retired later next year, so when I heard they were moving out west for a bit, I had to jump on one.

Today, I see what it's like to fly on Air Canada's smallest Dash 8!
